OL,3,CMum speaks of difficulty of three-year
OL,4,Cwait for young son's surgery
OL,6,F"He's got other health complications,
OL,7,Fso it often means he's hospitalised
OL,8,Fdue to high temperatures and
OL,9,Finfections. We've been on the urgent
OL,10,Flist for a very long time."
OL,12,FAccording to the latest statistics,
OL,13,Fthe longest waiting lists for planned
OL,14,FNHS treatments fell by more than a
OL,15,Fquarter in February.
OL,17,FIn February there were 15,505 cases
OL,18,Fwhere somebody had waited more than
OL,19,Ftwo years compared to more than 21,087
OL,20,Fin January - a decrease of more than
OL,21,F26%.
OL,1,Wj5hw}j5 ~shws                   G2/9
